The paper discusses the development of physically unclonable cryptographic primitives using memristive crossbar arrays. This topic falls under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper involves the use of electronic hardware and circuit design, which could fall under the categories of electronic devices and circuits (cs.ET), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), electromagnetics (cs.EM), and software engineering (cs.SE).
